24/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government adopted an action plan on Monday (23 December) for implementation of the Ohrid peace agreement. 
The plan, which will be discussed at Thursday's meeting of Ohrid signatories, reiterates the government's commitment to continuing the process of stabilisation and reform. 
It also sets terms for fulfilling the remaining legal obligations and confidence-building measures required by the accords. 
After input from all sides, the final version would be approved on 15 January. 
(Utrinski Vesnik - 24/12/02; A1 TV, MIA - 23/12/02)
